<subSubSection id="C329E097091A464EFF5ACA9BFF322795" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C091A464EFF5ACA9BFF322795" blockId="16.[151,1436,257,1074]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E091A464EFF5ACA9BFEAC27B9" bold="true" box="[197,331,941,965]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is descriptive for the very long, slender curved spine on the middle of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329E097091A464EFF5ACAC3FD0C204D" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C091A464EFF5ACAC3FD0C204D" blockId="16.[151,1436,257,1074]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E091A464EFF5ACAC3FEDE2071" bold="true" box="[197,313,1013,1037]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F091A464EFEDFCAC0FE252071" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[320,450,1013,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bolidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E091A464EFEDFCAC0FE252071" box="[320,450,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearest to 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F091A464EFDC6CAC0FD242071" box="[601,707,1014,1037]" class="Aves" family="Anatidae" genus="Cercopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anseriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurata">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E091A464EFDC6CAC0FD242071" box="[601,707,1014,1037]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. aurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be easily distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F091A464EFAD1CAC3FF26204D" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bolidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E091A464EFAD1CAC3FF26204D" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bolidiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very long spine on the aedeagus (Fig. 44).
</paragraph>
